{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-template-jsx","path":"/contact","webpackCompilationHash":"8f2d537de0bf718bfae7","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Cynthia Dominguez","subtitle":"Software Engineer","copyright":"© All rights reserved.","menu":[{"label":"Articles","path":"/"},{"label":"About me","path":"/about/"},{"label":"Portfolio","path":"/contact/"}],"author":{"name":"Cynthia Dominguez","email":"cmdominguez@gmail.com","twitter":"cynthiadomingz","github":"cynergist"}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"adb8a7db-0646-5ab0-871f-1c105e05b90e","html":"<h2>Simple Shell in C</h2>\n<p>I truly enjoyed creating a <a href=\"https://github.com/cynergist/simple_shell\">simple shell in C</a>, and would really like to do this again in Python, Ruby, or C++. There are a few reasons why this project was so informative. First, the exercise in building a shell in C did not allow use of C’s standard libraries.</p>\n<p>This was an interesting challenge because, when I needed to, for example, copy a string of characters to a new destination, instead of using <code class=\"language-text\">strcpy</code> from the <code class=\"language-text\">stdio.h</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">string.h</code> libraries, I had to create <a href=\"https://github.com/cynergist/simple_shell/blob/master/simple_helpers.c\">custom functions</a> that would do this for me. It was a useful exercise that helped me understand what is happening byte-by-byte when we have <code class=\"language-text\">argv</code> input from the command line and that input is tokenized and used to search the built-ins or PATH programs.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c3a25aad468e25db6f9f49903fe7c00c/5058c/shell_snip.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 45.16129032258064%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"This screenshot shows the simple shell handling the commands: ls, pwd, git status, rm, and exit.\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/c3a25aad468e25db6f9f49903fe7c00c/b3ee8/shell_snip.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c3a25aad468e25db6f9f49903fe7c00c/3bc27/shell_snip.jpg 240w,\n/static/c3a25aad468e25db6f9f49903fe7c00c/98431/shell_snip.jpg 480w,\n/static/c3a25aad468e25db6f9f49903fe7c00c/b3ee8/shell_snip.jpg 960w,\n/static/c3a25aad468e25db6f9f49903fe7c00c/b97fe/shell_snip.jpg 1440w,\n/static/c3a25aad468e25db6f9f49903fe7c00c/fb329/shell_snip.jpg 1920w,\n/static/c3a25aad468e25db6f9f49903fe7c00c/5058c/shell_snip.jpg 2604w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>It is important to know how much memory is being called because there may be a circumstance where we’re asked to build hardware that has a limit on the amount of memory it can provide (theoretically!).  For this reason, we used system calls only when necessary. My favorite system call from this project was <code class=\"language-text\">fork</code> because in order to use it, I learned:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>What the child process was doing while the parent would <code class=\"language-text\">wait</code>, and</li>\n<li>When the child needed to be terminated, and how.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ea8d72b2eac7a3dcd9d2e214f0aa5b41/6264d/shell_child.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 124.21991084695394%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"This screenshot shows the code using validation statements to test whether the current process is the child.\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ea8d72b2eac7a3dcd9d2e214f0aa5b41/b3ee8/shell_child.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ea8d72b2eac7a3dcd9d2e214f0aa5b41/3bc27/shell_child.jpg 240w,\n/static/ea8d72b2eac7a3dcd9d2e214f0aa5b41/98431/shell_child.jpg 480w,\n/static/ea8d72b2eac7a3dcd9d2e214f0aa5b41/b3ee8/shell_child.jpg 960w,\n/static/ea8d72b2eac7a3dcd9d2e214f0aa5b41/6264d/shell_child.jpg 1346w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Commands <br /></h2>\n<p>At minimum, this shell handles the following commands to display file contents on the command line: <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">cat</code>: Concatenates the file and gives output on standard output. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">less</code>: View files instead of opening the file. Allows backward and forward movement. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">more</code>: Page through text one screenful at a time. <br />\n<br />\nThis shell handles the following file and directory manipulation commands: <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">mkdir</code>: Creates a directory and accepts directory name as next parameter. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">rm</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">rm -r</code>: Used to delete files and directories. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">touch</code>: Creates a file or updates a file. <br />\n<br />\nAnd the following basic command line navigation commands: <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">ls</code>: Displays list of all files and folders in the current directory. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">cd</code>: Changes the directory. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">du</code>: Shows disk usage. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">pwd</code>: Shows the present working directory. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">man</code> + <code class=\"language-text\">cmd</code>: Shows the manual entry for any given command. <br />\n<code class=\"language-text\">exit</code>: Quits the simple_shell program. <br />\n<br />\nThe command <code class=\"language-text\">env</code> displays all environmental variables in the PATH: <br /></p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/de39620a30991a282471141b0b280496/8c64e/shell_env.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 23.980815347721823%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Snippet shows execution of env command.\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/de39620a30991a282471141b0b280496/b3ee8/shell_env.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/de39620a30991a282471141b0b280496/3bc27/shell_env.jpg 240w,\n/static/de39620a30991a282471141b0b280496/98431/shell_env.jpg 480w,\n/static/de39620a30991a282471141b0b280496/b3ee8/shell_env.jpg 960w,\n/static/de39620a30991a282471141b0b280496/b97fe/shell_env.jpg 1440w,\n/static/de39620a30991a282471141b0b280496/8c64e/shell_env.jpg 1668w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>My contributions to this project were:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The <a href=\"https://github.com/cynergist/simple_shell/blob/master/simple_shell.c\">main function</a></li>\n<li>The “helper”, or <a href=\"https://github.com/cynergist/simple_shell/blob/master/simple_helpers.c\">custom functions</a>, and</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"https://github.com/cynergist/simple_shell/blob/master/built_ins.c\">built-in functions</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Next features <br /></h2>\n<p>I am working on: <br /></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Dynamic memory allocation to eliminate memory leaks.</li>\n<li>Backspace ability for correcting arguments entered while in interactive mode.</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Portfolio","date":null,"description":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/contact"}}}